Stuttgart, Wolfsburg Win 3-0 to Open Season in German Bundesliga

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-08-06T18:38:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-06/stuttgart-wolfsburg-win-3-0-to-open-season-in-german-bundesliga.html
Stuttgart and Wolfsburg were 3-0
winners in their opening games of the season in German soccer’s
Bundesliga.  Cacau, Martin Hamik and Shinji Okazaki scored the goals in
Stuttgart’s home win over Schalke, while Patrik Helmes had two
goals in Wolfsburg’s win in Cologne.  Newly promoted Augsburg tied 2-2 with Freiburg, Werder
Bremen beat Kailserslautern 2-0, Hannover defeated Hoffenheim 2-
1 and Nuremberg won 1-0 at promoted Hertha Berlin.  Dortmund opened defense of its title with a 3-1 win over
Hamburg last night. Bayern Munich hosts Moenchengladbach and
 Bayer Leverkusen  visits Mainz in tomorrow’s games.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  